==Arabic==
===Etymology I===
From {{ARchar|[[جد#Noun|جد]]}} (jadd), [[grandfather]], [[ancestor]].

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|جدة}}''' (jídda) {{f}}, {{ARchar|[[جدات]]}} (jiddāt) {{p}}

# [[grandmother]]
# [[Eve]] (wife of Adam)
# [[Jeddah]] (port city in Saudi Arabia on the Red Sea, purportedly the burial site of [[Eve]])

===Etymology II===
From the root verb {{ARchar|[[جد#Verb|جد]]}} (jádda), to be [[new]].

===Noun===
'''{{ARchar|جدة}}''' (jídda) {{f}}

# [[newness]], [[recency]]
# [[novelty]]
# [[modernness]], [[modernity]]
# [[rebirth]], [[renaissance]]

